<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddcb7f4c0-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06" identifier="/us/usc/t12/s1884"><num value="1884">§ 1884.</num><heading> Penalties for violations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A bank or savings association which violates a rule promulgated pursuant to this chapter shall be subject to a civil penalty which shall not exceed $100 for each day of the violation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddcb7f4c1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/389/s5">Pub. L. 90–389, § 5</ref>, <date date="1968-07-07">July 7, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/295">82 Stat. 295</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/203/tIII/s356/3">Pub. L. 111–203, title III, § 356(3)</ref>, <date date="2010-07-21">July 21, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/1547">124 Stat. 1547</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="iddcb7f4c2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06">
